{"search_data": "Central, HaryanaPradhan Mantri Suraksha Bima Yojana \u2013 Accidental Insurance Scheme in HaryanaIn case of complete loss of eye-sight of both eyes or loss of both hands/feet due to the accident, the scheme will provide an insurance amount of Rs. 2 lakh.If the person loses his eye-sight of one eye or loses one hand/feet in the accident, an insurance cover of Rs. 1 lakh will be provided under the PMSBY scheme.To get the above insurance covers, the applicants will have to pay the annual premium of Rs. 12 only.Eligibility Criteria of PMSBY HaryanaTo be eligible for the scheme, the applicant will have to fulfill the following eligibility of the insurance scheme.The applicant should be an adult (18+ Years) to get the insurance cover under the scheme.The maximum age to get the insurance cover in the scheme is 70 years (nearest birthday).The applicant must have a saving bank account linked with his/her Aadhaar Card. Aadhaar is a primary KYC for the bank account and insurance coverage.Enrollment Period for PMSBYThe premium of Rs. 12 will be deducted from the account holder\u2019s savings bank account through \u2018auto-debit\u2019 facility on or before 1st June each year for the coverage of one year. And the government will deposit the insurance cover to the beneficiary\u2019s account through the direct credit policy.The insurance coverage would be for one year period stretching from 1 June to 31 May.Consent form to join, pay, auto-debit from the designated savings bank account on the prescribed forms will be required to be given by the beneficiary by May 31 of every year.Termination of Cover under PMSBYThe beneficiary attains the age of 70 years.Closing of bank beneficiary\u2019s bank account due to insufficient balance.In case, the beneficiary is covered through more than one of his/her accounts."}